============================================================
PART 1 — CREATE S3 BUCKET + UPLOAD OBJECT + ENABLE PUBLIC
============================================================
------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 1 — OPEN S3
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Login to AWS Management Console
2) In search bar type:
   S3
3) Click:
   Amazon S3
4) Click:
   Create bucket
------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 2 — BUCKET CONFIGURATION
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Bucket name:
   my-public-bucket-123
   (Must be globally unique)

2) Region:
   Choose nearest region

------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 3 — DISABLE BLOCK PUBLIC ACCESS (IMPORTANT)
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Scroll to:
   Block Public Access settings
2) Click:
   Edit
3) UNCHECK:
   Block all public access
4) Confirm:
   ✔ I acknowledge that this bucket will become public
5) Click:
   Save changes

6) Click:
   Create bucket

Bucket created.


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 4 — ENABLE BUCKET ACL (PUBLIC READ)
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Click bucket name.
2) Go to:
   Permissions tab
3) Scroll to:
   Access Control List (ACL)
4) Click:
   Edit
5) Under Public access:
   ✔ Everyone (public access) → Read
6) Click:
   Save changes

Bucket is now publicly readable.


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 5 — UPLOAD OBJECT
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Go to:
   Objects tab
2) Click:
   Upload
3) Click:
   Add files
4) Select file (example: image.jpg)
5) Click:
   Upload


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 6 — ENABLE OBJECT PUBLIC ACCESS
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Click uploaded object.
2) Go to:
   Permissions tab
3) Scroll to:
   Access Control List (ACL)
4) Click:
   Edit
5) Under Public access:
   ✔ Everyone (public access) → Read
6) Click:
   Save changes


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 7 — VERIFY PUBLIC ACCESS
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Go to:
   Objects tab
2) Click object.
3) Copy:
   Object URL
4) Open browser in Incognito mode.
5) Paste URL.

Object should open without login.


============================================================
PART 2 — ENABLE S3 VERSIONING
============================================================

------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 1 — ENABLE VERSIONING
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Open S3.
2) Select bucket.
3) Go to:
   Properties tab
4) Scroll to:
   Bucket Versioning
5) Click:
   Edit
6) Select:
   Enable
7) Click:
   Save changes

Versioning enabled.


------------------------------------------------------------
OUTPUT SCENARIO
------------------------------------------------------------

A) Upload report.pdf
   → Version ID automatically assigned.

B) Upload report.pdf again (same name)
   → Old version preserved.
   → New version becomes current.

C) Delete report.pdf
   → Delete Marker created.
   → Older versions still available under:
     Objects → Show versions


============================================================
PART 3 — CROSS-REGION REPLICATION (CRR)
============================================================

PREREQUISITES:
✔ Versioning enabled on BOTH buckets
✔ Buckets must be in different regions


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 1 — CREATE DESTINATION BUCKET
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Go to:
   S3 → Create bucket
2) Bucket name:
   dest-crr-bucket
3) Choose DIFFERENT region
4) Click:
   Create bucket
5) Enable Versioning (same steps as above)


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 2 — CREATE REPLICATION RULE
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Open SOURCE bucket.
2) Go to:
   Management tab
3) Click:
   Replication rules
4) Click:
   Create replication rule


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 3 — CONFIGURE RULE
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Rule name:
   academy-crr-rule
2) Status:
   Enabled
3) IAM Role:
   Select existing role → labrole
4) Scope:
   Apply to all objects


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 4 — CHOOSE DESTINATION
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Select:
   Another bucket
2) Choose:
   dest-crr-bucket
3) Confirm different region
4) Select:
   Use AWS-managed role / default role
5) Click:
   Save

Replication rule active.


------------------------------------------------------------
VERIFY CRR
------------------------------------------------------------

1) Upload new file (example: image.png) to SOURCE bucket.
2) Open DESTINATION bucket.
3) File appears automatically.
4) Version ID present.

Replication successful.


============================================================
PART 4 — STATIC WEBSITE HOSTING IN S3
============================================================

Files required:
index.html
error.html


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 1 — CREATE BUCKET
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Go to:
   S3 → Create bucket
2) Bucket name:
   my-static-site-bucket-123
3) Choose region
4) Under Block Public Access:
   UNCHECK Block all public access
5) Confirm acknowledgment
6) Click:
   Create bucket


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 2 — UPLOAD WEBSITE FILES
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Open bucket.
2) Go to:
   Objects
3) Click:
   Upload
4) Add files:
   index.html
   error.html
5) Click:
   Upload


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 3 — ENABLE STATIC WEBSITE HOSTING
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Go to:
   Properties tab
2) Scroll to:
   Static website hosting
3) Click:
   Edit
4) Select:
   Enable
5) Choose:
   Host a static website
6) Index document:
   index.html
7) Error document:
   error.html
8) Click:
   Save changes


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 4 — ENABLE BUCKET PUBLIC ACCESS (ACL)
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Go to:
   Permissions tab
2) Scroll to:
   Access Control List (ACL)
3) Click:
   Edit
4) Under Public access:
   ✔ Everyone → Read
5) Save changes


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 5 — ENABLE OBJECT PUBLIC ACCESS
------------------------------------------------------------
For index.html:
1) Click object.
2) Go to:
   Permissions
3) Edit ACL
4) ✔ Everyone → Read
5) Save

Repeat same steps for:
error.html


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 6 — ACCESS WEBSITE
------------------------------------------------------------
1) Go to:
   Properties
2) Scroll to:
   Static website hosting
3) Copy:
   Bucket website endpoint
4) Paste into browser.

index.html loads.


------------------------------------------------------------
STEP 7 — TEST ERROR PAGE
------------------------------------------------------------
1) In browser, type:
   http://bucket-name.s3-website-region.amazonaws.com/invalid.html
2) Press Enter.

error.html page should display.

Static website working successfully.
